                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-308-off1581 t18280911-308-victim1682"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>JAMES FRANKLIN. I was <rs id="t18280911-308-viclabel1583" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-308-victim1682 t18280911-308-viclabel1583"></join> to Mr. Flower, of Bedford-place, on the 24th of June. The prisoner lodged there on the 24th of June; when I went out I locked my apartment, and when I returned my window was broken, and the shoes gone - I put up a board with a gimblet, and on the 30th, when I came home, the board was removed, and the four shoes were gone; the prisoner did not return that night - he came the next morning, but I did not see him again till the 8th of August, when I saw him in Oxford-street; I challenged him with it - he denied it; I met him again with his wife a short time afterwards, and said I intended to take him up on suspicion, and said, I was the last person he should have thought of doing such a thing to, as I had been a friend to him; he was then taken up, and confessed that he took those on the 24th of June, and pawned them on the 26th, and those on the 30th he sold to a Jew.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-308-person1683">
                  THOMAS 
                  HENRY THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18280911-308-person1683" type="surname" value="HENRY THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-308-person1683" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-308-person1683" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner; he said he took the four shoes, and sold them to a Jew in the street.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I did not steal them, and never said I did.</p>
